Exit Polls
On an Election Day in the midst of a devastating pandemic and a clash of competing visions of America, fear was the great uniter, and motivator.
Along with falling short of expectations in the Senate, Democrats saw their House majority shrink.
Investors pushed up stocks of companies they believed would be protected by a Republican Senate, even if Joe Biden wins the presidency.
Although some are still too close to call, they’re tilting in Joe Biden’s direction for now.
Here’s where things stand on Day 2.
President Trump and his aides have been critical of the cable network that includes some of his most ardent media allies.
The lowest number of chambers changed hands in more than half a century.
President Trump won the state by a larger margin than in 2016.
Some suburban strongholds have swung back to the G.O.P. in New York and across the country.
A rumor floated by internet conservatives about the use of felt-tip markers by Arizona polling stations isn’t true, officials say.
